nment strategies are used in region\nmerging and splitting scenarios. Shape changes between aligned regions are\ndescribed by contour metamorphosis. Specifically, local spatial deformation is\nmodeled by PDE and computed using level-set methods. Directional predictions\nare obtained using particle trajectories by following the evolving boundary.\nHowever, when a branching point is encountered, particles may lose track of the\nwavefront. To overcome this, a curvelet backtracking algorithm has been\nproposed to recover information for boundary segments without particle coverage\nto minimize shape distortion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 6 Jun 2020 01:39:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-09"}
