 of the maximum power for a typical indoor mmWave cluster, a\npractical beamwidth of 3.5 deg is enough. Finally, our analysis results show\nthat there is a 13 dB increase in the maximum theoretical received power when\nUPA is used over ULA. We show that an 8 x 8 UPA can reach 50% of that maximum\nreceived power while the received power is still 10 dB larger than the ULA\nscenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Jun 2020 18:48:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-11"}
